             were indicted for <rs id="t18300218-164-off913" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300218-164-off913" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300218-164-off913" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18300218-164-cd914" type="crimeDate">8th of February</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300218-164-off913 t18300218-164-cd914"></join>, 1 handkerchief, value 3s., the goods of a person unknown, from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>DANIEL FORRESTER. I am a City officer. On the 8th of February I saw the two prisoners in the <placeName id="t18300218-164-crimeloc915">Poultry</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300218-164-crimeloc915" type="placeName" value="Poultry"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300218-164-crimeloc915" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300218-164-off913 t18300218-164-crimeloc915"></join>, about twelve o'clock - they crossed and followed a gentleman towards St. Paul's; they then returned, and followed another gentleman. who had a handkerchief partly out of his pocket - when they came near Mr. Debatt's shop they closed upon him; I seized them, and found this handkerchief on Helston - I took the gentleman to the Mansion-house; he gave the name of Mayer, No. 13, Birchin-lane -I asked him to come, but he did not; I went to that address, but the gentleman had gone away - the prisoners were close together; one must have seen what the other did - Helston had it in his apron.</p>
               <p>Thomas put in a written defence, stating that he met Helston in a crowd, caused by a coach having broken down - that they walked together, when two men passed them and threw the handkerchief at their feet.</p>
               <p>DANIEL FORRESTER. No one could have done it but them - there was no broken down coach there.</p>
               <p>HELSTON-<rs id="t18300218-164-verdict916" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300218-164-verdict916" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 17.</p>
               <p>THOMAS-<rs id="t18300218-164-verdict917" type="verdictDescription">
